.git
.gitignore
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.superpowers
.vscode
.idea
README.md

# Build output / deps — matched at ANY depth. The build context is the repo
# ROOT (see docker-compose.e2e.yml `context: ../../` and the Dockerfile build
# args), so Docker reads THIS .dockerignore and patterns must use **/ to match
# nested workspace paths like apps/web/node_modules. A bare `node_modules`
# only matches the context root and would let the nested copies through.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/*.log
# Repo-level docs only — **/docs also swallowed apps/website/src/app/docs
# (the API-reference route) out of the image. Anchor to the root.
/docs
**/tests

# Local SQLite dev DBs MUST NOT be baked into the image. The dev DB holds real
# user rows; if copied to apps/web/bookkeeprr.dev.db inside the image it makes
# every "fresh" e2e container start with a user, so the first-run gate is
# skipped and the whole e2e suite cascades red. (Prod is unaffected because it
# sets BOOKKEEPRR_DB_PATH=/config/..., but we still must not ship dev data.)
**/bookkeeprr.dev.db
**/bookkeeprr.dev.db-*
**/*.db
**/*.db-wal
**/*.db-shm
